 This install applies to "Lotus Esprit Turbo Challenge" © 1990 Gremlin
                                                               Magnetic Fields.

 This install requires WHDLoad, DIC, RawDIC and The Patcher to be in the path.
 The programs can be found in the WHDLoad package.
 To install from a different drive than DF0: select installation mode Expert.

 The installed program requires 0.5 MB ChipMem and 0.5 MB OtherMem.
 It can be quit by pressing F10 (key can be changed with Tooltype "QuitKey=").

 If you have problems with this installation please try and get a newer
 version of this package from the WHDLoad WWW-Page. If that doesn't help try
 some Tooltypes like NOCACHE, NOAUTOVEC, EXPCHIP, NOMMU, PAL or NTSC. If
 that also fails, please inform the author via the Bug-Report-Form which
 can be accessed on the WHDLoad WWW-Page.

 For the full WHDLoad package, other installs and updates refer to:
        http://www.whdload.de/
 or     aminet:dev/misc/whdload#?
 and    aminet:game/patch/

 version 1.1 (03.06.06) done by CFou:
 - Self-modifying code patches fixed for 68060 with 'Cache' tooltype
   ('Cache' tooltype can be needed for 2PL game)
 - CUSTOM2=1 tooltype used to remove SMC & Blitter waits patches
   (CUSTOM2 can be needed for slow CPU like 68000 if game is too slow) 

 version 1.0 (12.09.05) done by CFou:
 - initial release
 - 3 versions supported (2 disk versions & Lotus Trilogy CD32)
 - Using rawdic imager
 - Game fixed to run with cpu caches (Tested only on 68030)
 - Freeze with cpu caches fixed (CPU Interuption problem)
 - Keyboard routine fixed
 - Only for register users
  (no registered users can play only first level but without opponents)
 - Several blitter delays inserted
 - Several Self-modifying code fixed
 - Both stacks relocated in fast memory
 - CUSTOM1=1 Tooltype used to activated SkipLevel's key (F9)
 - CUSTOM1=2 Tooltype used to activated original cheat mode
 - CUSTOM1=3 Tooltype used to activated both previous option
    (In this previous cases High Scores are not saved)
 - CUSTOM1=4 Tooltype used to activated original sub-game mode
 - Original sub-game patched too ;)
        - Keyboard routine inserted
        - Black screen bug on aga fixed
 - Manual&Hints Files added
 - Tested in snoop mode
 - Some icons included (Thanks to Frank)

 version 0.94 done by Wepl & Harry
 - One version supported
 - ButtonWait Tooltype used to insert press fire delay before race
 - Load/Save High Score redirected on HD (file 'Highs')
 - Some Self-Modifying code fixed
 - Some blitter delay inserted

 Thanks to: Wepl, Harry & JOTD for beta source
            Frank for his beautiful icons
